Detailed Description

cvmx_usbc::_gahbcfg

Core AHB Configuration Register (GAHBCFG)

This register can be used to configure the core after power-on or a change in mode of operation. This register mainly contains AHB system-related configuration parameters. The AHB is the processor interface to the O2P USB core. In general, software need not know about this interface except to program the values as specified.

The application must program this register as part of the O2P USB core initialization. Do not change this register after the initial programming.
